The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Two youths, carrying 5kg ganja, a pipegun and ammunition, were arrested in Lake Town and Baguiati on Sunday evening. Prasenjit Goldar and Samir Das and another youth were riding a bike without helmets. When ASI Ranjit Kar stopped them near Lake Town, they started running towards the airport. The cop caught Goldar. Das got into a taxi that sped towards the airport while the other youth disappeared into an alley. Kar took a motorcycle from a bystander and chased the taxi, intercepted it at Baguiati crossing and arrested Das. The pipegun and a bullet were found on him. The ganja was found on the abandoned motorcycle.    Sheikh Nizamuddin, a 59-year-old cancer patient, died after falling from the third floor of a building in the Calcutta Medical College and Hospital compound on Sunday. Police suspect the resident of Mullickpur in South 24-Parganas had committed suicide.    The body of a youth named Dukhiram Pal was found beside NH6, in Uluberia, on Sunday. Police said the Pal, a resident of the area, might have died after being hit by a car.    Mayor Sovan Chatterjee announced on Sunday that the CMC would increase the number of National Old Age Pension Scheme recipients to 45,975. Currently, 22,131 people receive the pension.                                                                                                                                               
